HEADWORD: Heterosis
<hw>Het`e*ro"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ alteration, fr. <?/ other, different.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A figure of speech by which one form of a noun, verb, or pronoun,
and the like, is used for another, as in the sentence: ⟦ldquo⟧What is
life to such as <xex>me</xex>?⟦rdquo⟧</def>
<rj><au>Aytoun.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

